    "title": "The White House Has a Bowling Alley, a Movie Theater, and a Ghost",
    "summary": "The White House contains 132 rooms, a bowling alley, a movie theater, a swimming pool, and allegedly the ghost of Abraham Lincoln. Multiple presidents, first ladies, and foreign dignitaries have reported seeing him.",
    "fullText": "The White House is not just the president's office -- it is a 55,000-square-foot residence packed with amenities and oddities accumulated over more than two centuries. There is a bowling alley (installed by Nixon), a movie theater (FDR), a swimming pool (Ford), a chocolate shop, a florist, and a full-time calligrapher. The building has 132 rooms, 35 bathrooms, and 412 doors. It also has a long-standing reputation for being haunted, with the ghost of Abraham Lincoln being the most frequently reported apparition. Queen Wilhelmina of the Netherlands allegedly fainted after seeing Lincoln's ghost at her bedroom door. Winston Churchill reportedly refused to sleep in the Lincoln Bedroom after an encounter. Eleanor Roosevelt claimed she could feel Lincoln's presence in the room. Whether or not ghosts are real, the sheer number of credible witnesses who have reported seeing Lincoln in the White House is, at minimum, a fascinating psychological phenomenon.",
