    "id": "mw-tx-012",
    "lat": 29.5588,
    "lng": -98.4563,
    "title": "The Biggest Cowboy Boots You Will Ever See",
    "summary": "A pair of giant cowboy boots stands 40 feet tall outside North Star Mall in San Antonio. They are the largest cowboy boots in the world and they are gloriously absurd.",
    "fullText": "Artist Bob Wade created the World's Largest Cowboy Boots in 1980 as a public art installation outside North Star Mall in San Antonio. Each boot stands about 40 feet tall and is made of concrete, rebar, and plaster over a steel frame. The boots are modeled after actual ostrich-skin cowboy boots and weigh several tons each. Wade was known for his oversized Texana sculptures, including a giant iguana and a massive pair of frogs. The boots have become one of San Antonio's most recognizable landmarks and a mandatory photo stop. They perfectly capture the Texas ethos that if something is worth doing, it is worth overdoing.",
    "category": "landmark",
    "year": "1980",
